The paper deals with the problem of multiple sparse linear regression, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics. The use of regularization techniques and the analysis of sample complexity are also mentioned, which are common themes in the subfield of statistical learning theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which are also relevant to the topic. Additionally, the paper presents empirical results and theoretical guarantees, which suggest that it could also be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), depending on the specific focus of the research.
